00:40:37.870 --> 00:40:40.080
Definitely had a positive
impact on the user

00:40:40.080 --> 00:40:40.700
experience, right?

00:40:40.700 --> 00:40:44.319
Making a bad situation
slightly less bad.

00:40:44.319 --> 00:40:47.109
But the real improvement
came from when they focused

00:40:47.109 --> 00:40:48.760
on reliability, right?

00:40:48.760 --> 00:40:52.240
They committed as a team to
making the service much more

00:40:52.240 --> 00:40:54.549
reliable, to making it
something that you can

00:40:54.549 --> 00:40:57.390
depend on and it paid
off big for them.

00:40:57.390 --> 00:41:00.339
Partially as a result I
think of the reliability

00:41:00.339 --> 00:41:01.839
improvements.

00:41:01.839 --> 00:41:04.009
Twitter is now not
seen as a toy.

00:41:04.009 --> 00:41:05.869
It's seen as an essential
tool for a lot of people.

00:41:05.869 --> 00:41:09.039
It's seen as this incredible
platform for communication.

00:41:09.039 --> 00:41:12.039
And now it's at the point where
I can't remember the last time

00:41:12.039 --> 00:41:15.059
that I saw the fail whale
except for when I was making

00:41:15.059 --> 00:41:18.299
this presentation of course.

00:41:18.299 --> 00:41:19.469
So that wraps it up.

00:41:19.469 --> 00:41:20.889
We talked about
seven principles.

00:41:20.889 --> 00:41:23.739
We scattered some tips and
some examples in there.

00:41:23.739 --> 00:41:25.299
The first one to be fast.

00:41:25.299 --> 00:41:27.299
Not only should your
application be fast, but you

00:41:27.299 --> 00:41:30.479
should allow your users to
be fast at using it.

00:41:30.479 --> 00:41:31.389
You should be yourself.

00:41:31.389 --> 00:41:33.529
You should let the spirit
and the personality of

00:41:33.529 --> 00:41:35.189
the developers come
out in the product.

00:41:35.189 --> 00:41:36.529
That wil give you
a point of view.

00:41:36.529 --> 00:41:38.889
It will give your users
something to relate to.

00:41:38.889 --> 00:41:40.759
Engage in conversations
with your users.

00:41:40.759 --> 00:41:42.839
Figure out what they're
experiencing, what they're

00:41:42.839 --> 00:41:44.869
going through, and
talk with them.

00:41:44.869 --> 00:41:47.819
Be willing to give up control
in those cases where it can

00:41:47.819 --> 00:41:49.460
actually result in a
better experience.

00:41:49.460 --> 00:41:52.259
Like where you get your artwork
from somewhere else because

00:41:52.259 --> 00:41:54.519
you can't do it yourself.

00:41:54.519 --> 00:41:54.719
Be polite.

00:41:54.719 --> 00:41:55.669
Be considerate.

00:41:56.559 --> 00:41:58.959
Think about things from the
perspective of your users.

00:41:58.959 --> 00:42:00.389
Make it easy for them
to get started.

00:42:00.389 --> 00:42:02.179
Make it easy for them
to leave or get out of

00:42:02.179 --> 00:42:03.619
whatever they're doing.

00:42:03.619 --> 00:42:06.869
Prepare for the likely event
that your users will fail, will

00:42:06.869 --> 00:42:09.719
run into a problem while
they're using your application

00:42:09.719 --> 00:42:11.299
and try to work around that.

00:42:11.299 --> 00:42:13.259
And finally, be reliable.

00:42:13.259 --> 00:42:16.170
So that your users can
actually use the product

00:42:16.170 --> 00:42:19.399
that you created.

00:42:19.399 --> 00:42:20.040
Thank you.

00:42:20.040 --> 00:42:21.044
That's it.

