00:47:16.289 --> 00:47:16.649
Yes sir?

00:47:16.649 --> 00:47:18.569
AUDIENCE: Yeah, when you were
talking about making text

00:47:18.569 --> 00:47:21.819
friendly, how do you
handle localizing text?

00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:25.409
You know, where it says
something that's more cultural?

00:47:25.409 --> 00:47:27.159
MATT SHOBE: Well that
is a challenge.

00:47:27.159 --> 00:47:34.089
I think the reality of having
a personality of course it

00:47:34.089 --> 00:47:36.550
has a lot of cultural
connotations to it.

00:47:36.550 --> 00:47:39.359
Like I was thinking we had
a section on FeedBurner

00:47:39.359 --> 00:47:40.919
that was my feeds blank.

00:47:40.919 --> 00:47:43.409
And we'd always put some phrase
in there and it was typically

00:47:43.409 --> 00:47:49.409
something vaguely seasonal or
it might have a slight baseball

00:47:49.409 --> 00:47:53.659
reference or I stuck in a
TK-421-Y enter at your

00:47:53.659 --> 00:47:54.989
post at one point.

00:47:54.989 --> 00:47:58.270
And you know, that was for the
five people that got that.

00:47:58.270 --> 00:48:01.010
And so that part of it is just
kind of saying we're not going

00:48:01.010 --> 00:48:02.830
to be predictable here.

00:48:02.830 --> 00:48:07.469
And I think if you have an
organization that is building a

00:48:07.469 --> 00:48:09.960
product that's going to be
localized, you may simply not

00:48:09.960 --> 00:48:13.249
get the same benefits in effect
unless your localizers

00:48:13.249 --> 00:48:14.309
are in on it.

00:48:16.410 --> 00:48:18.339
Whatever that sense
is can translate.

00:48:18.339 --> 00:48:20.660
If there's a humorous aspect
to it that's always tricky.

00:48:20.660 --> 00:48:23.709
I mean, I don't know that I'd
ever promise success there.

00:48:25.229 --> 00:48:27.799
We want it to be whimsical
and playful and empathetic.

00:48:27.799 --> 00:48:30.889
We want to feel like if you
could somehow communicate

00:48:30.889 --> 00:48:32.520
to the folks that are
doing the translation.

00:48:32.950 --> 00:48:36.359
Part of the apps need to read
like it's really on your side.

00:48:36.359 --> 00:48:38.539
However that can be nuanced,
I'd take a chance at trying

00:48:38.539 --> 00:48:40.389
to do that because that's
ultimately what you're trying

00:48:40.389 --> 00:48:42.430
to communicate in any language.

00:48:42.430 --> 00:48:44.499
JOHN ZERATSKY: It's
definitely harder though.

00:48:44.499 --> 00:48:45.369
MATT SHOBE: Yeah, I
certainly don't have a

00:48:45.369 --> 00:48:47.890
pat solution for that.

00:48:47.890 --> 00:48:51.929
Although I hear our Russian
translator was hilarious.

00:48:51.929 --> 00:48:54.239
AUDIENCE: Hello, I wanted to
ask if you had any experience

00:48:54.239 --> 00:48:58.500
